{
  "texts": [
    "In 2019, Ma et al. [57] proposed GPN, integrating GNN and Ptr-Net to tackle large-scale TSP and TSPTW.",
    "In 2020, Drori et al. [58] proposed a framework based on GAT.",
    "In 2021, Ouyang et al. [59] addressed the issue of input invariance, augmenting input through rotation, flipping, scaling, and translation, and utilized GNN to tackle TSP, exhibiting strong generalization capability.",
    "In 2024, Lischka et al. [54] presented a novel approach highlighting the significance of sparsification for GNNs for TSP.In 2023, Sun and Yang [60] introduced DIFUSCO, a graphbased diffusion solver, tailored for resolving large-scale TSP instances.Also in 2023, Liu et al.",
    "[61] proposed AdaSolver, aimed at improving the generalization capabilities of exact solvers for combinatorial optimization problems.In summary, these algorithms provide diverse approaches to construct TSP solutions, integrating SL or RL, and embracing attention mechanism, Ptr-Net, Transformer, GNN, generative and adversarial models."
  ]
}